<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="658" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[113,1089,220,563]" pageId="13" pageNumber="658">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,242,284,307]" pageId="13" pageNumber="658">Etymology.</emphasis>
Species is dedicated to Petr Bulirsch (
<collectingRegion box="[670,748,284,307]" country="Czech Republic" name="Praha" pageId="13" pageNumber="658">Prague</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[762,939,284,307]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="13" pageNumber="658">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
), a 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[981,1089,284,307]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Carabidae</taxonomicName>
specialist, who provided an extensive material of small sifted entimines from 
<collectingCountry box="[952,1089,316,339]" name="South Africa" pageId="13" pageNumber="658">South Africa</collectingCountry>
to the first author.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[113,702,380,403]" pageId="13" pageNumber="658" type="biology_ecology">
