<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="658" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[113,1089,220,563]" pageId="13" pageNumber="658">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,370,444,467]" pageId="13" pageNumber="658">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species is characterized by elytral setae on apical declivity semiappressed, rostrum in males distinctly enlarged anteriad, at apex equally wide as head including eyes, and by penis short, at apex regularly triangular, in basal half concave. This set of characters easily distinguishes 
<taxonomicName authority="Borovec &amp; Skuhrovec, 2017" authorityName="Borovec &amp; Skuhrovec" authorityYear="2017" box="[504,627,540,563]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Epistomius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bulirschi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[504,627,540,563]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="658">E. bulirschi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[633,715,540,563]" pageId="13" pageNumber="658" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from all other species of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
